FAQs about hotels in Orlando

On average, 3-star hotels in Orlando cost $135 per night, and 4-star hotels in Orlando are $217 per night. If you're looking for something really special, a 5-star hotel in Orlando can be found for $746 per night, on average (based on Booking.com prices).
The average price per night for a 3-star hotel in Orlando this weekend is $185 or, for a 4-star hotel, $323. Looking for something even fancier? 5-star hotels in Orlando for this weekend cost around $979 per night, on average (based on Booking.com prices).
On average, it costs $162 per night to book a 3-star hotel in Orlando for tonight. You'll pay around $338 if you choose to stay in a 4-star hotel tonight, while a 5-star hotel in Orlando will cost around $1,129, on average (based on Booking.com prices).
Many families visiting Orlando loved staying at Aloft Orlando Lake Nona , Marriott's Cypress Harbour Villas , and Hampton Inn By Hilton Ocoee Orlando .
Some of the best hotels in Orlando near Downtown Disney include Drury Plaza Hotel Orlando - Disney Springs Area , Marriott's Sabal Palms and Sheraton Vistana Resort Villas, Lake Buena Vista Orlando .
Travelers who stayed in Orlando near Orlando International Airport (MCO) have said good things about Hyatt Regency Orlando International Airport Hotel , Hyatt House Orlando Airport , and Marriott Orlando Airport Lakeside .
Drury Plaza Hotel Orlando - Disney Springs Area , Hyatt House Orlando Airport , and Residence Inn by Marriott Orlando at FLAMINGO CROSSINGS Town Center are some of the popular hotels in Orlando.
For hotels in Orlando that serve highly-rated breakfasts, try Marriott's Royal Palms , TownePlace Suites by Marriott Orlando Airport , and Hampton Inn Lake Buena Vista / Orlando .
These hotels in Orlando are highly rated by couples: Courtyard by Marriott Orlando Lake Nona , Home2 Suites By Hilton Orlando Near UCF , and Fairfield Inn & Suites by Marriott Orlando East/UCF Area .
Marriott's Royal Palms , Home2 Suites By Hilton Orlando Near UCF , and Staybridge Suites Orlando at SeaWorld by IHG - Free Parking & Shuttle to Seaworld Parks got great room view-related reviews from travelers in Orlando.

  • Review score
    6.0

    We have been visiting Orlando for over twenty five years...

    We have been visiting Orlando for over twenty five years with four children and now as a couple. It seems to us to get worse every time. We visited last November and again last week. Food prices in the bars and restaurants had greatly increased in that short time. It's now really expensive. Restaurants all now push for 18, 22 or 28% tip!! As a Brit, I really don't agree! I've been vegetairian for most of my life. The big appeal for me has always been the mix of people and cultures in Orlando. Six years ago, I could walk into any restaurant on I drive and be given a vegetairian menu consisting of 6 to 10 proper meal choices. Now the attitude is that "you won't leave hungry". Even restaurants that offer "vege" dishes now state they are cooked in fat previously used for meat or fish! Unacceptable to any vegetairian!! We went to Uncle Julio last week - it has lots of vege choices on it's menu. I asked the server for a recommendation - told "salad", declined and then offered a plate of nachos, declined again. Offerered a quasidilla but only with cheese and onions in it!! We left and went to another chain - the Yard House. This time the vege food was cooked in meat or fish fat so we left again. There are some hidden jems - The Broadway pizza in Kissemmee. We've been visiting for many years and it's always the same - just some reasonable increases to the price. Really friendly staff always willing to offer a wine recommendation! We had tickets for Universal this time. Unfortunately we clashed with Spring break - should have known better! Queues were up to two hours for the rides. Too many people are buying express passes! Everyone else has to queue so much longer. This is too much standing for us. After having many great holidays in Orlando we are really considering not returning. With Joann closing and TJ maxx closed and I can't enjoy a cooked meal out, why come to Orlando?
    Guest review by
    Coral
    United Kingdom

How does it work?

  • 1

    It starts with a booking

    It starts with a booking

    The only way to leave a review is to first make a booking. That's how we know our reviews come from real guests who have stayed at the property.

  • 2

    Followed by a trip

    Followed by a trip

    When guests stay at the property, they check out how quiet the room is, how friendly the staff is, and more.

  • 3

    And finally, a review

    And finally, a review

    After their trip, guests tell us about their stay. We check for naughty words and verify the authenticity of all guest reviews before adding them to our site.

If you booked through us and want to leave a review, please sign in first.
